<TITLE> Iftekhar condemns Maldives attack on Bangladeshi </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 24 (bdnews24.com)  Foreign Adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury Friday condemned the alleged attacks on Bangladeshi workers in the Maldives which left one dead. The adviser spoke by telephone to the Bangladesh High Commissioner in Male, Mijarul Quayes, and directed him to monitor the situation carefully and report back. The envoy reported to the Chowdhury that the Maldivian authorities had assured him that the incident was being "thoroughly investigated" and that the "culprits would be punished". He sent a letter to the Maldivian foreign minister urging necessary steps to ensure safety and security of Bangladeshi workers there. bdne
